-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-14/galatasaray-surges-fenerbahce-falls-after-match-correct-.html
(Corrects share price in last paragraph.)  Galatasaray Sportif Sinai & Ticari
Yatirimlar AS (GSRAY) , the merchandising unit of soccer team
Galatasaray, surged in Istanbul after the team won Turkey’s
soccer championship at the weekend.  Galatasaray Sportif jumped 10 percent to 218.5 liras at
9:50 a.m., in the biggest increase since March 29. Galatasaray
became this season’s champion in Turkey’s top soccer league
after a goalless draw with local rival Fenerbahce on May 12.  Fenerbahce Sportif Hizmetler Sanayi & Ticaret AS (FENER)  slid 7.8
percent to 53.25 liras, falling the most since Dec. 5.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aydan Eksin in Istanbul at 
